From fdda5eaa59b9503aec403eb365a16725885c008e Sat Jun 26 11:34:09 2021 +0530
From: Karthikeyan Periyasamy <periyasa@codeaurora.org
Date: Sat Jun 26 11:34:09 2021 +0530
Subject: ath11k: avoid stack corruption in ath11k_dp_rx_h_undecap_nwifi

In ath11k_dp_rx_h_undecap_nwifi(), local array decap_hdr get copied
beyond the array size 30 when QoS data recieved in 4adrr format.
In 4addr format the max header length is 36. So increase the array
size as 36 to avoid local array overflow

Change-Id: I5941738b21ae235f5feec0b650a40300b14e1041
Signed-off-by: Karthikeyan Periyasamy <periyasa@codeaurora.org>
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/dp_rx.h
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/dp_rx.h
@@ -9,7 +9,7 @@
 #include "rx_desc.h"
 #include "debug.h"
 
-#define DP_MAX_NWIFI_HDR_LEN	30
+#define DP_MAX_NWIFI_HDR_LEN	36
 
 #define DP_RX_MPDU_ERR_FCS			BIT(0)
 #define DP_RX_MPDU_ERR_DECRYPT			BIT(1)
